## Overview
Implement the TypeScript/TSX parser that detects documentation components (JSX with headings) vs code components (exports), extracting the appropriate structure from each.

## Dependencies
- Parser interface and utilities must exist

## Files to Create

### `internal/parser/typescript.go`
```go
package parser

import "regexp"

// Compile regex patterns once at package init
var (
    jsxHeadingRegex = regexp.MustCompile(\`<h([1-6])[^>]*>(.*?)</h\1>\`)
    exportRegex     = regexp.MustCompile(\`(?m)^\s*export\s+(const|function|interface|type|class)\s+(\w+)\`)
    jsdocRegex      = regexp.MustCompile(\`(?s)/\*\*\s*\n(.*?)\*/\`)
    jsxTagStripper  = regexp.MustCompile(\`<[^>]+>\`)
)

type TypeScriptParser struct{}

func NewTypeScriptParser() *TypeScriptParser { return &TypeScriptParser{} }

func (p *TypeScriptParser) CanParse(path string) bool {
    ft := DetectFileType(path)
    return ft == "tsx" || ft == "ts"
}

func (p *TypeScriptParser) Parse(path string, content []byte) (*ParseResult, error) {
    // 1. StripBOM
    // 2. Count lines
    // 3. Extract JSX headings using jsxHeadingRegex
    //    - For each match: get heading level (group 1), text (group 2)
    //    - Strip nested tags from text using jsxTagStripper
    //    - Calculate line number by counting newlines before match position
    // 4. Determine component type:
    //    - If >= 2 headings with non-empty text -> documentation component
    //    - Otherwise -> code component
    // 5. If documentation component:
    //    - Description = first <h1> text, or first heading text
    //    - Outline = headings list
    // 6. If code component:
    //    - Extract exports using exportRegex
    //    - Description from JSDoc (jsdocRegex) or first comment
    //    - Outline = exports list
    // 7. Return ParseResult with appropriate ComponentType
}

// Helper: calculate line number from byte offset in content
func lineNumberAt(content []byte, offset int) int { ... }
```

### `internal/parser/typescript_test.go`
Table-driven tests:
- TSX documentation component (multiple JSX headings like <h1>Title</h1>)
- TSX code component (exports, interfaces)
- TSX with JSDoc comment
- TSX with nested tags in headings (e.g., <h1><code>foo</code> bar</h1>)
- TSX with only imports (no headings, no exports)
- TS file with exports
- TS file with JSDoc
- TSX with exactly 1 heading (should be code component)
- TSX with exactly 2 headings (should be documentation component)
- Empty file

